<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-545-564  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 545 564.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  August 21 1989 n329 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The name's the game is systems software.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ellison, Alec L.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Software publishers are often frustrated that users seem to drawno conclusion between a software package they own and the companywho sold it to them.andP;  Leading vendors in the systems softwarearena are beginning to deal with this problem with a well-knownconsumer marketing technique, called umbrella branding or lineextensions.andP;  This means that common brand labels are applied torelated products.andP;  The job of selling additional products to acompany's existing user base is made much easier by tying thecompany name to all products.andP;  Umbrella branding also increasesthe importance of marketing strategy.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Software PublishersMarketing StrategyBrand NameProduct Life CycleSystems Software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>